  "prompt": "How do I delete snapchat conversation without using clear conversations?",
  "response": "Here are the steps to delete a Snapchat conversation without using the \"Clear Conversations\" feature:\n\n1. Open the Snapchat conversation you want to delete\n\n2. Tap and hold the specific message you want to remove\n\n3. Select \"Delete\" from the pop-up menu\n\n4. Choose \"Delete for Me\" or \"Delete for Everyone\" depending on your preference\n\n5. Repeat this process for individual messages you want to remove\n\nAlternatively, you can:\n- Swipe the conversation to the right\n- Tap the trash can icon to delete the entire conversation\n\nRemember that deleting messages this way is manual and takes more time compared to clearing conversations, but it allows more precise control over which messages are removed.",
